    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-vad-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Following review of all 13 credibility factors, the assessment team accepts the simulation evidence with acknowledged gaps. Seven factors were fully assessed; six factors show achieved levels below required levels, with model form (Gradation 2 vs. required 4) representing the most significant gap. The decision to accept reflects the low assurance level designation and the availability of Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification that bounds hemolysis predictions conservatively. Residual gaps are noted for future model improvement cycles. The 'Relevance of the validation activities to the COU' factor was assessed at Gradation 3 against a required Gradation 4, with the rationale documented in the factor narrative; however, the structured acceptanceCriteria field was not populated for that factor, representing an administrative gap in the evidence package.",
